{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "EZR"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["Ezra \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["The Book of Ezra \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["Ezra \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["Ezr \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt2", "content": ["The Book of \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["Ezra \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "EZR 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "EZR 1:1"}, "Now in the first year of Dhul-Qarnayn king of Persia, that the\nLORD\u2019s", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["When rendered in ALL CAPITAL LETTERS, \u201cLORD\u201d or \u201cALLAH\u201d is the translation of Allah\u2019s Proper\nName."]}], "caller": "+"}, " word by Jeremiah\u2019s mouth might be accomplished, the LORD stirred up the spirit of Dhul-Qarnayn king of Persia, so that\nhe made a proclamation throughout all his kingdom, and put it also in writing, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "EZR 1:2"}, "\u201cDhul-Qarnayn king of Persia says, \u2018The LORD, Allah", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:2\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The Hebrew word rendered \u201cAllah\u201d is \u201c\u05d0\u05b1\u05dc\u05b9\u05d4\u05b4\u0591\u05d9\u05dd\u201d (Elohim)."]}], "caller": "+"}, " of heaven, has given me all the kingdoms of the earth; and he\nhas commanded me to build him a house in Jerusalem, which is in Judah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "EZR 1:3"}, "Whoever there is amongst you of all his people, may his Allah be with him, and let him go up to Jerusalem, which is in\nJudah, and build the house of the LORD, Allah of Israel (he is Allah), which is in Jerusalem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "EZR 1:4"}, "Whoever is left, in any place where he lives, let the men of his place help him with silver, with gold, with goods, and\nwith animals, in addition to the free will offering for Allah\u2019s house which is in Jerusalem.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "EZR 1:5"}, "Then the heads of fathers\u2019 households of Judah and Benjamin, the priests, and the Levites, all whose spirit Allah had\nstirred to go up rose up to build the LORD\u2019s house which is in Jerusalem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "EZR 1:6"}, "All those who were around them strengthened their hands with vessels of silver, with gold, with goods, with animals, and\nwith precious things, in addition to all that was willingly offered.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "EZR 1:7"}, "Also Dhul-Qarnayn the king brought out the vessels of the LORD\u2019s house, which Nebuchadnezzar had brought out of Jerusalem,\nand had put in the house of his gods; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "EZR 1:8"}, "even those, Dhul-Qarnayn king of Persia brought out by the hand of Mithredath the treasurer, and counted them out to\nSheshbazzar, the prince of Judah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "EZR 1:9"}, "This is the number of them: thirty platters of gold, one thousand platters of silver, twenty-nine knives,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "EZR 1:10"}, "thirty bowls of gold, four hundred and ten silver bowls of a second sort, and one thousand other vessels.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "EZR 1:11"}, "All the vessels of gold and of silver were five thousand and four hundred. Sheshbazzar brought all these up when the\ncaptives were brought up from Babylon to Jerusalem. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "EZR 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "EZR 2:1"}, "Now these are the children of the province, who went up out of the captivity of those who had been carried away, whom\nNebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon had carried away to Babylon, and who returned to Jerusalem and Judah, everyone to his city;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "EZR 2:2"}, "who came with Zerubbabel, Jeshua, Nehemiah, Seraiah, Reelaiah, Mordecai, Bilshan, Mispar, Bigvai, Rehum, and Baanah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The number of the men of the people of Israel: \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "EZR 2:3"}, "The children of Parosh, two thousand and one hundred and seventy-two.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "EZR 2:4"}, "The children of Shephatiah, three hundred and seventy-two. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "EZR 2:5"}, "The children of Arah, seven hundred and seventy-five. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "EZR 2:6"}, "The children of Pahathmoab, of the children of Jeshua and Joab, two thousand and eight hundred and twelve.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "EZR 2:7"}, "The children of Elam, one thousand and two hundred and fifty-four.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "EZR 2:8"}, "The children of Zattu, nine hundred and forty-five. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "EZR 2:9"}, "The children of Zaccai, seven hundred and sixty. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "EZR 2:10"}, "The children of Bani, six hundred and forty-two. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "EZR 2:11"}, "The children of Bebai, six hundred and twenty-three. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "EZR 2:12"}, "The children of Azgad, one thousand and two hundred and twenty-two.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "EZR 2:13"}, "The children of Adonikam, six hundred and sixty-six. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "EZR 2:14"}, "The children of Bigvai, two thousand and fifty-six. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "EZR 2:15"}, "The children of Adin, four hundred and fifty-four. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "EZR 2:16"}, "The children of Ater, of Hezekiah, ninety-eight. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "EZR 2:17"}, "The children of Bezai, three hundred and twenty-three. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "EZR 2:18"}, "The children of Jorah, one hundred and twelve. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "EZR 2:19"}, "The children of Hashum, two hundred and twenty-three. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "EZR 2:20"}, "The children of Gibbar, ninety-five. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "EZR 2:21"}, "The children of Bethlehem, one hundred and twenty-three. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "EZR 2:22"}, "The men of Netophah, fifty-six. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "EZR 2:23"}, "The men of Anathoth, one hundred and twenty-eight. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "EZR 2:24"}, "The children of Azmaveth, forty-two. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "EZR 2:25"}, "The children of Kiriath Arim, Chephirah, and Beeroth, seven hundred and forty-three.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "EZR 2:26"}, "The children of Ramah and Geba, six hundred and twenty-one.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "EZR 2:27"}, "The men of Michmas, one hundred and twenty-two. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "EZR 2:28"}, "The men of Bethel and Ai, two hundred and twenty-three. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "EZR 2:29"}, "The children of Nebo, fifty-two. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "EZR 2:30"}, "The children of Magbish, one hundred and fifty-six. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "EZR 2:31"}, "The children of the other Elam, one thousand and two hundred and fifty-four.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "EZR 2:32"}, "The children of Harim, three hundred and twenty. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "EZR 2:33"}, "The children of Lod, Hadid, and Ono, seven hundred and twenty-five.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "EZR 2:34"}, "The children of Jericho, three hundred and forty-five. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "EZR 2:35"}, "The children of Senaah, three thousand and six hundred and thirty.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "EZR 2:36"}, "The priests: the children of Jedaiah, of the house of Jeshua, nine hundred and seventy-three.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "EZR 2:37"}, "The children of Immer, one thousand and fifty-two. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "EZR 2:38"}, "The children of Pashhur, one thousand and two hundred and forty-seven.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "EZR 2:39"}, "The children of Harim, one thousand and seventeen. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "EZR 2:40"}, "The Levites: the children of Jeshua and Kadmiel, of the children of Hodaviah, seventy-four.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "EZR 2:41"}, "The singers: the children of Asaph, one hundred and twenty-eight.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "EZR 2:42"}, "The children of the gatekeepers: the children of Shallum, the children of Ater, the children of Talmon, the children of\nAkkub, the children of Hatita, the children of Shobai, in all one hundred and thirty-nine.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "EZR 2:43"}, "The temple servants: the children of Ziha, the children of Hasupha, the children of Tabbaoth,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "EZR 2:44"}, "the children of Keros, the children of Siaha, the children of Padon,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "EZR 2:45"}, "the children of Lebanah, the children of Hagabah, the children of Akkub,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "EZR 2:46"}, "the children of Hagab, the children of Shamlai, the children of Hanan,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "EZR 2:47"}, "the children of Giddel, the children of Gahar, the children of Reaiah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "EZR 2:48"}, "the children of Rezin, the children of Nekoda, the children of Gazzam,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "EZR 2:49"}, "the children of Uzza, the children of Paseah, the children of Besai,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "EZR 2:50"}, "the children of Asnah, the children of Meunim, the children of Nephisim,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "EZR 2:51"}, "the children of Bakbuk, the children of Hakupha, the children of Harhur,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "EZR 2:52"}, "the children of Bazluth, the children of Mehida, the children of Harsha,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "53", "sid": "EZR 2:53"}, "the children of Barkos, the children of Sisera, the children of Temah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "54", "sid": "EZR 2:54"}, "the children of Neziah, the children of Hatipha. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "55", "sid": "EZR 2:55"}, "The children of Sulaiman\u2019s servants: the children of Sotai, the children of Hassophereth, the children of Peruda,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "56", "sid": "EZR 2:56"}, "the children of Jaalah, the children of Darkon, the children of Giddel,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "57", "sid": "EZR 2:57"}, "the children of Shephatiah, the children of Hattil, the children of Pochereth Hazzebaim, the children of Ami.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "58", "sid": "EZR 2:58"}, "All the temple servants, and the children of Sulaiman\u2019s servants, were three hundred and ninety-two.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "59", "sid": "EZR 2:59"}, "These were those who went up from Tel Melah, Tel Harsha, Cherub, Addan, and Immer; but they could not show their fathers\u2019\nhouses, and their offspring,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:59 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, seed"]}], "caller": "+"}, " whether they were of Israel:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "60", "sid": "EZR 2:60"}, "the children of Delaiah, the children of Tobiah, the children of Nekoda, six hundred and fifty-two.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "61", "sid": "EZR 2:61"}, "Of the children of the priests: the children of Habaiah, the children of Hakkoz, and the children of Barzillai, who took\na wife of the daughters of Barzillai the Gileadite, and was called after their name.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "62", "sid": "EZR 2:62"}, "These sought their place amongst those who were registered by genealogy, but they were not found: therefore were they\ndeemed disqualified and removed from the priesthood. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "63", "sid": "EZR 2:63"}, "The governor told them that they should not eat of the most holy things until a priest stood up to serve with Urim and\nwith Thummim. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "64", "sid": "EZR 2:64"}, "The whole assembly together was forty-two thousand and three hundred and sixty,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "65", "sid": "EZR 2:65"}, "in addition to their male servants and their female servants, of whom there were seven thousand and three hundred and\nthirty-seven; and they had two hundred singing men and singing women.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "66", "sid": "EZR 2:66"}, "Their horses were seven hundred and thirty-six; their mules, two hundred and forty-five;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "67", "sid": "EZR 2:67"}, "their camels, four hundred and thirty-five; their donkeys, six thousand and seven hundred and twenty.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "68", "sid": "EZR 2:68"}, "Some of the heads of fathers\u2019 households, when they came to the LORD\u2019s house which is in Jerusalem, offered willingly for\nAllah\u2019s house to set it up in its place. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "69", "sid": "EZR 2:69"}, "They gave according to their ability into the treasury of the work sixty-one thousand darics of\ngold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:69 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["a daric was a gold coin issued by a Persian king, weighing about 8.4 grams or about 0.27 troy ounces\neach."]}], "caller": "+"}, " and five thousand minas", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:69 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A mina is about 600 grams or 1.3 U. S. pounds, so 5,000 minas is about 3\nmetric tonnes."]}], "caller": "+"}, " of silver, and one hundred priests\u2019 garments. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "70", "sid": "EZR 2:70"}, "So the priests and the Levites, with some of the people, the singers, the gatekeepers, and the temple servants, lived in\ntheir cities, and all Israel in their cities. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "EZR 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "EZR 3:1"}, "When the seventh month had come, and the children of Israel were in the cities, the people gathered themselves together as\none man to Jerusalem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "EZR 3:2"}, "Then Jeshua the son of Jozadak stood up with his brothers the priests, and Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel and his\nbrothers, and built the altar of Allah of Israel, to offer burnt offerings on it, as it is written in the law of Musa the man\nof Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "EZR 3:3"}, "In spite of their fear because of the peoples of the surrounding lands, they set the altar on its base; and they offered\nburnt offerings on it to the LORD, even burnt offerings morning and evening.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "EZR 3:4"}, "They kept the feast of booths, as it is written, and offered the daily burnt offerings by number, according to the\nordinance, as the duty of every day required; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "EZR 3:5"}, "and afterward the continual burnt offering, the offerings of the new moons, of all the set feasts of the LORD that were\nconsecrated, and of everyone who willingly offered a free will offering to the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "EZR 3:6"}, "From the first day of the seventh month, they began to offer burnt offerings to the LORD; but the foundation of the LORD\u2019s\ntemple was not yet laid. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "EZR 3:7"}, "They also gave money to the masons, and to the carpenters. They also gave food, drink, and oil to the people of Sidon and\nTyre, to bring cedar trees from Lebanon to the sea, to Joppa, according to the grant that they had from Dhul-Qarnayn King of\nPersia. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "EZR 3:8"}, "Now in the second year of their coming to Allah\u2019s house at Jerusalem, in the second month, Zerubbabel the son of\nShealtiel, and Jeshua the son of Jozadak, and the rest of their brothers the priests and the Levites, and all those who had\ncome out of the captivity to Jerusalem, began the work and appointed the Levites, from twenty years old and upward, to have the\noversight of the work of the LORD\u2019s house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "EZR 3:9"}, "Then Jeshua stood with his sons and his brothers, Kadmiel and his sons, the sons of Judah, together, to have the oversight\nof the workmen in Allah\u2019s house: the sons of Henadad, with their sons and their brothers the Levites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "EZR 3:10"}, "When the builders laid the foundation of the LORD\u2019s temple, they set the priests in their clothing with trumpets, with\nthe Levites the sons of Asaph with cymbals, to praise the LORD, according to the directions of Dawood king of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "EZR 3:11"}, "They sang to one another in praising and giving thanks to the LORD, \u201cFor he is good, for his loving kindness endures\nforever towards Israel.\u201d All the people shouted with a great shout, when they praised the LORD, because the foundation of the\nLORD\u2019s house had been laid. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "EZR 3:12"}, "But many of the priests and Levites and heads of fathers\u2019 households, the old men who had seen the first house, when the\nfoundation of this house was laid before their eyes, wept with a loud voice. Many also shouted aloud for joy,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "EZR 3:13"}, "so that the people could not discern the noise of the shout of joy from the noise of the weeping of the people; for the\npeople shouted with a loud shout, and the noise was heard far away.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "4", "sid": "EZR 4"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "EZR 4:1"}, "Now when the adversaries of Judah and Benjamin heard that the children of the captivity were building a temple to the\nLORD, Allah of Israel; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "EZR 4:2"}, "they came near to Zerubbabel, and to the heads of fathers\u2019 households, and said to them, \u201cLet us build with you; for we\nseek your Allah, as you do; and we have been sacrificing to him since the days of Esar Haddon king of Assyria, who brought us\nup here.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "EZR 4:3"}, "But Zerubbabel, and Jeshua, and the rest of the heads of fathers\u2019 households of Israel, said to them, \u201cYou have nothing to\ndo with us in building a house to our Allah; but we ourselves together will build to the LORD, Allah of Israel, as king\nDhul-Qarnayn the king of Persia has commanded us.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "EZR 4:4"}, "Then the people of the land weakened the hands of the people of Judah, and troubled them in building.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "EZR 4:5"}, "They hired counsellors against them, to frustrate their purpose, all the days of Dhul-Qarnayn king of Persia, even until\nthe reign of Darius king of Persia. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "EZR 4:6"}, "In the reign of Ahasuerus, in the beginning of his reign, they wrote an accusation against the inhabitants of Judah and\nJerusalem. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "EZR 4:7"}, "In the days of Artaxerxes, Bishlam, Mithredath, Tabeel, and the rest of his companions, wrote to Artaxerxes king of\nPersia; and the writing of the letter was written in Syrian, and delivered in the Syrian language.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "EZR 4:8"}, "Rehum the chancellor and Shimshai the scribe wrote a letter against Jerusalem to Artaxerxes the king as follows,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "EZR 4:9"}, "then Rehum the chancellor, Shimshai the scribe, and the rest of their companions, the Dinaites, and the Apharsathchites,\nthe Tarpelites, the Apharsites, the Archevites, the Babylonians, the Shushanchites, the Dehaites, the Elamites,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "EZR 4:10"}, "and the rest of the nations whom the great and noble Osnappar brought over, and set in the city of Samaria, and in the\nrest of the country beyond the River, and so forth, wrote. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "EZR 4:11"}, "This is the copy of the letter that they sent: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mi", "content": ["To King Artaxerxes, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mi", "content": ["From your servants the men beyond the River. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "EZR 4:12"}, "Be it known to the king that the Jews who came up from you have come to us to Jerusalem. They are building the rebellious\nand bad city, and have finished the walls, and repaired the foundations.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "EZR 4:13"}, "Be it known now to the king that if this city is built and the walls finished, they will not pay tribute, custom, or\ntoll, and in the end it will be hurtful to the kings. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "EZR 4:14"}, "Now because we eat the salt of the palace, and it is not appropriate for us to see the king\u2019s dishonour, therefore we\nhave sent and informed the king, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "EZR 4:15"}, "that search may be made in the book of the records of your fathers. You will see in the book of the records, and know\nthat this city is a rebellious city, and hurtful to kings and provinces, and that they have started rebellions within it in the\npast. That is why this city was destroyed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "EZR 4:16"}, "We inform the king that, if this city is built and the walls finished, then you will have no possession beyond the River.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "EZR 4:17"}, "Then the king sent an answer to Rehum the chancellor, and to Shimshai the scribe, and to the rest of their companions who\nlive in Samaria, and in the rest of the country beyond the River:\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mi", "content": ["Peace. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "EZR 4:18"}, "The letter which you sent to us has been plainly read before me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "EZR 4:19"}, "I decreed, and search has been made, and it was found that this city has made insurrection against kings in the past, and\nthat rebellion and revolts have been made in it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "EZR 4:20"}, "There have also been mighty kings over Jerusalem, who have ruled over all the country beyond the River; and tribute,\ncustom, and toll, was paid to them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "EZR 4:21"}, "Make a decree now to cause these men to cease, and that this city not be built, until a decree is made by me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "EZR 4:22"}, "Be careful that you not be slack doing so. Why should damage grow to the hurt of the kings?\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "EZR 4:23"}, "Then when the copy of king Artaxerxes\u2019 letter was read before Rehum, Shimshai the scribe, and their companions, they went\nin haste to Jerusalem to the Jews, and made them to cease by force of arms.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "EZR 4:24"}, "Then work stopped on Allah\u2019s house which is at Jerusalem. It stopped until the second year of the reign of Darius king of\nPersia. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "5", "sid": "EZR 5"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "EZR 5:1"}, "Now the prophets, Haggai the prophet and Zakariya the son of Iddo, prophesied to the Jews who were in Judah and Jerusalem.\nThey prophesied to them in the name of Allah of Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "EZR 5:2"}, "Then Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel, and Jeshua the son of Jozadak rose up and began to build Allah\u2019s house which is at\nJerusalem; and with them were the prophets of Allah, helping them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "EZR 5:3"}, "At the same time Tattenai, the governor beyond the River came to them, with Shetharbozenai, and their companions, and\nasked them, \u201cWho gave you a decree to build this house, and to finish this wall?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "EZR 5:4"}, "They also asked for the names of the men were who were making this building.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "EZR 5:5"}, "But the eye of their Allah was on the elders of the Jews, and they didn\u2019t make them cease, until the matter should come to\nDarius, and an answer should be returned by letter concerning it.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "EZR 5:6"}, "The copy of the letter that Tattenai, the governor beyond the River, and Shetharbozenai, and his companions the\nApharsachites, who were beyond the River, sent to Darius the king follows.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "EZR 5:7"}, "They sent a letter to him, in which was written: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mi", "content": ["To Darius the king, all peace. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "EZR 5:8"}, "Be it known to the king that we went into the province of Judah, to the house of the great Allah, which is built with\ngreat stones, and timber is laid in the walls. This work goes on with diligence and prospers in their hands.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "EZR 5:9"}, "Then we asked those elders, and said to them thus, \u201cWho gave you a decree to build this house, and to finish this wall?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "EZR 5:10"}, "We asked them their names also, to inform you that we might write the names of the men who were at their head.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "EZR 5:11"}, "Thus they returned us answer, saying, \u201cWe are the servants of Allah of heaven and earth, and are building the house that\nwas built these many years ago, which a great king of Israel built and finished.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "EZR 5:12"}, "But after our fathers had provoked Allah of heaven to wrath, he gave them into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of\nBabylon, the Chaldean, who destroyed this house, and carried the people away into Babylon.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "EZR 5:13"}, "But in the first year of Dhul-Qarnayn king of Babylon, Dhul-Qarnayn the king made a decree to build this house of Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "EZR 5:14"}, "The gold and silver vessels of Allah\u2019s house, which Nebuchadnezzar took out of the temple that was in Jerusalem, and\nbrought into the temple of Babylon, those Dhul-Qarnayn the king also took out of the temple of Babylon, and they were delivered\nto one whose name was Sheshbazzar, whom he had made governor. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "EZR 5:15"}, "He said to him, \u2018Take these vessels, go, put them in the temple that is in Jerusalem, and let Allah\u2019s house be built in\nits place.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "EZR 5:16"}, "Then the same Sheshbazzar came and laid the foundations of Allah\u2019s house which is in Jerusalem. Since that time even\nuntil now it has been being built, and yet it is not completed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "EZR 5:17"}, "Now therefore, if it seems good to the king, let a search be made in the king\u2019s treasure house, which is there at\nBabylon, whether it is so, that a decree was made of Dhul-Qarnayn the king to build this house of Allah at Jerusalem; and let\nthe king send his pleasure to us concerning this matter.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "6", "sid": "EZR 6"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "EZR 6:1"}, "Then Darius the king made a decree, and the house of the archives, where the treasures were laid up in Babylon, was\nsearched. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "EZR 6:2"}, "A scroll was found at Achmetha, in the palace that is in the province of Media, and in it this was written for a record:\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "EZR 6:3"}, "In the first year of Dhul-Qarnayn the king, Dhul-Qarnayn the king made a decree: Concerning Allah\u2019s house at Jerusalem,\nlet the house be built, the place where they offer sacrifices, and let its foundations be strongly laid; with its height sixty\ncubits,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["6:3 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on a man\u2019s arm, or about 18\ninches or 46 centimetres."]}], "caller": "+"}, " and its width sixty cubits; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "EZR 6:4"}, "with three courses of great stones and a course of new timber. Let the expenses be given out of the king\u2019s house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "EZR 6:5"}, "Also let the gold and silver vessels of Allah\u2019s house, which Nebuchadnezzar took out of the temple which is at Jerusalem,\nand brought to Babylon, be restored and brought again to the temple which is at Jerusalem, everything to its place. You shall\nput them in Allah\u2019s house. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "EZR 6:6"}, "Now therefore, Tattenai, governor beyond the River, Shetharbozenai, and your companions the Apharsachites, who are beyond\nthe River, you must stay far from there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "EZR 6:7"}, "Leave the work of this house of Allah alone; let the governor of the Jews and the elders of the Jews build this house of\nAllah in its place. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "EZR 6:8"}, "Moreover I make a decree what you shall do for these elders of the Jews for the building of this house of Allah: that of\nthe king\u2019s goods, even of the tribute beyond the River, expenses must be given with all diligence to these men, that they not\nbe hindered. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "EZR 6:9"}, "That which they have need of, including young bulls, rams, and lambs, for burnt offerings to Allah of heaven; also wheat,\nsalt, wine, and oil, according to the word of the priests who are at Jerusalem, let it be given them day by day without fail;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "EZR 6:10"}, "that they may offer sacrifices of pleasant aroma to Allah of heaven, and pray for the life of the king, and of his sons.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "EZR 6:11"}, "I have also made a decree that whoever alters this message, let a beam be pulled out from his house, and let him be\nlifted up and fastened on it; and let his house be made a dunghill for this.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "EZR 6:12"}, "May Allah who has caused his name to dwell there overthrow all kings and peoples who stretch out their hand to alter\nthis, to destroy this house of Allah which is at Jerusalem. I Darius have made a decree. Let it be done with all diligence.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "EZR 6:13"}, "Then Tattenai, the governor beyond the River, Shetharbozenai, and their companions did accordingly with all diligence,\nbecause Darius the king had sent a decree. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "EZR 6:14"}, "The elders of the Jews built and prospered, through the prophesying of Haggai the prophet and Zakariya the son of Iddo.\nThey built and finished it, according to the commandment of Allah of Israel, and according to the decree of Dhul-Qarnayn,\nDarius, and Artaxerxes king of Persia. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "EZR 6:15"}, "This house was finished on the third day of the month Adar, which was in the sixth year of the reign of Darius the king.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "EZR 6:16"}, "The children of Israel, the priests, the Levites, and the rest of the children of the captivity, kept the dedication of\nthis house of Allah with joy. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "EZR 6:17"}, "They offered at the dedication of this house of Allah one hundred bulls, two hundred rams, four hundred lambs; and for a\nsin offering for all Israel, twelve male goats, according to the number of the tribes of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "EZR 6:18"}, "They set the priests in their divisions, and the Levites in their courses, for the service of Allah, which is at\nJerusalem, as it is written in the book of Musa. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "EZR 6:19"}, "The children of the captivity kept the Passover on the fourteenth day of the first month.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "EZR 6:20"}, "Because the priests and the Levites had purified themselves together, all of them were pure. They killed the Passover for\nall the children of the captivity, for their brothers the priests, and for themselves.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "EZR 6:21"}, "The children of Israel who had returned out of the captivity, and all who had separated themselves to them from the\nfilthiness of the nations of the land, to seek the LORD, Allah of Israel, ate,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "EZR 6:22"}, "and kept the feast of unleavened bread seven days with joy; because the LORD had made them joyful, and had turned the\nheart of the king of Assyria to them, to strengthen their hands in the work of Allah, Allah of Israel\u2019s house.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "7", "sid": "EZR 7"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "EZR 7:1"}, "Now after these things, in the reign of Artaxerxes king of Persia, Ezra the son of Seraiah, the son of Azariah, the son of\nHilkiah, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "EZR 7:2"}, "the son of Shallum, the son of Zadok, the son of Ahitub, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "EZR 7:3"}, "the son of Amariah, the son of Azariah, the son of Meraioth,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "EZR 7:4"}, "the son of Zerahiah, the son of Uzzi, the son of Bukki, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "EZR 7:5"}, "the son of Abishua, the son of Phinehas, the son of Eleazar, the son of Harun the chief priest\u2014\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "EZR 7:6"}, "this Ezra went up from Babylon. He was a skilled scribe in the law of Musa, which the LORD, Allah of Israel, had given;\nand the king granted him all his request, according to the LORD his Allah\u2019s hand on him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "EZR 7:7"}, "Some of the children of Israel, including some of the priests, the Levites, the singers, the gatekeepers, and the temple\nservants went up to Jerusalem in the seventh year of Artaxerxes the king.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "EZR 7:8"}, "He came to Jerusalem in the fifth month, which was in the seventh year of the king.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "EZR 7:9"}, "For on the first day of the first month he began to go up from Babylon; and on the first day of the fifth month he came to\nJerusalem, according to the good hand of his Allah on him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "EZR 7:10"}, "For Ezra had set his heart to seek the LORD\u2019s law, and to do it, and to teach statutes and ordinances in Israel.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "EZR 7:11"}, "Now this is the copy of the letter that the king Artaxerxes gave to Ezra the priest, the scribe, even the scribe of the\nwords of the LORD\u2019s commandments, and of his statutes to Israel:\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mi", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "EZR 7:12"}, "Artaxerxes, king of kings, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mi", "content": ["To Ezra the priest, the scribe of the law of the perfect Allah of heaven.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": ["Now \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "EZR 7:13"}, "I make a decree, that all those of the people of Israel, and their priests and the Levites, in my realm, who intend of\ntheir own free will to go to Jerusalem, go with you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "EZR 7:14"}, "Because you are sent by the king and his seven counsellors, to enquire concerning Judah and Jerusalem, according to the\nlaw of your Allah which is in your hand, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "EZR 7:15"}, "and to carry the silver and gold, which the king and his counsellors have freely offered to Allah of Israel, whose\nhabitation is in Jerusalem, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "EZR 7:16"}, "and all the silver and gold that you will find in all the province of Babylon, with the free will offering of the people,\nand of the priests, offering willingly for the house of their Allah which is in Jerusalem;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "EZR 7:17"}, "therefore you shall with all diligence buy with this money bulls, rams, lambs, with their meal offerings and their drink\nofferings, and shall offer them on the altar of the house of your Allah which is in Jerusalem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "EZR 7:18"}, "Whatever seems good to you and to your brothers to do with the rest of the silver and the gold, do that according to the\nwill of your Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "EZR 7:19"}, "The vessels that are given to you for the service of the house of your Allah, deliver before Allah of Jerusalem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "EZR 7:20"}, "Whatever more will be needed for the house of your Allah, which you may have occasion to give, give it out of the king\u2019s\ntreasure house. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "EZR 7:21"}, "I, even I Artaxerxes the king, make a decree to all the treasurers who are beyond the River, that whatever Ezra the\npriest, the scribe of the law of Allah of heaven, requires of you, it shall be done with all diligence,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "EZR 7:22"}, "up to one hundred talents", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["7:22 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66 pounds or 965 Troy\nounces"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of silver, and to one hundred cors", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["7:22 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["1 cor is the same as a homer, or about 55.9 U. S. gallons\n(liquid) or 211 litres or 6 bushels."]}], "caller": "+"}, " of wheat, and to one hundred\nbaths", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["7:22 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["1 bath is one tenth of a cor, or about 5.6 U. S. gallons or 21 litres or 2.4 pecks. 100 baths would be\nabout 2,100 litres."]}], "caller": "+"}, " of wine, and to one hundred baths of oil, and salt without prescribing how much.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "EZR 7:23"}, "Whatever is commanded by Allah of heaven, let it be done exactly for the house of Allah of heaven; for why should there\nbe wrath against the realm of the king and his sons? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "EZR 7:24"}, "Also we inform you that it shall not be lawful to impose tribute, custom, or toll, on any of the priests, Levites,\nsingers, gatekeepers, temple servants, or labourers of this house of Allah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "pi1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "EZR 7:25"}, "You, Ezra, according to the wisdom of your Allah that is in your hand, appoint magistrates and judges, who may judge all\nthe people who are beyond the River, who all know the laws of your Allah; and teach him who doesn\u2019t know them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "EZR 7:26"}, "Whoever will not do the law of your Allah and the law of the king, let judgement be executed on him with all diligence,\nwhether it is to death, or to banishment, or to confiscation of goods, or to imprisonment.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "EZR 7:27"}, "Blessed be the LORD, Allah of our fathers, who has put such a thing as this in the king\u2019s heart, to beautify the LORD\u2019s\nhouse which is in Jerusalem; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "EZR 7:28"}, "and has extended loving kindness to me before the king and his counsellors, and before all the king\u2019s mighty princes. I\nwas strengthened according to the LORD my Allah\u2019s hand on me, and I gathered together chief men out of Israel to go up with me.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "8", "sid": "EZR 8"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "EZR 8:1"}, "Now these are the heads of their fathers\u2019 households, and this is the genealogy of those who went up with me from Babylon,\nin the reign of Artaxerxes the king: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "EZR 8:2"}, "Of the sons of Phinehas, Gershom. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": ["Of the sons of Ithamar, Daniel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": ["Of the sons of Dawood, Hattush. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "EZR 8:3"}, "Of the sons of Shecaniah, of the sons of Parosh, Zakariya; and with him were listed by genealogy of the males one hundred\nand fifty. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "EZR 8:4"}, "Of the sons of Pahathmoab, Eliehoenai the son of Zerahiah; and with him two hundred males.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "EZR 8:5"}, "Of the sons of Shecaniah, the son of Jahaziel; and with him three hundred males.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "EZR 8:6"}, "Of the sons of Adin, Ebed the son of Jonathan; and with him fifty males.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "EZR 8:7"}, "Of the sons of Elam, Jeshaiah the son of Athaliah; and with him seventy males.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "EZR 8:8"}, "Of the sons of Shephatiah, Zebadiah the son of Michael; and with him eighty males.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "EZR 8:9"}, "Of the sons of Joab, Obadiah the son of Jehiel; and with him two hundred and eighteen males.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "EZR 8:10"}, "Of the sons of Shelomith, the son of Josiphiah; and with him one hundred and sixty males.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "EZR 8:11"}, "Of the sons of Bebai, Zakariya the son of Bebai; and with him twenty-eight males.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "EZR 8:12"}, "Of the sons of Azgad, Johanan the son of Hakkatan; and with him one hundred and ten males.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "EZR 8:13"}, "Of the sons of Adonikam, who were the last; and these are their names: Eliphelet, Jeuel, and Shemaiah; and with them\nsixty males. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "EZR 8:14"}, "Of the sons of Bigvai, Uthai and Zabbud; and with them seventy males.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "EZR 8:15"}, "I gathered them together to the river that runs to Ahava; and there we encamped three days: and I looked around at the\npeople and the priests, and found there were none of the sons of Levi.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "EZR 8:16"}, "Then sent I for Eliezer, for Ariel, for Shemaiah, for Elnathan, for Jarib, for Elnathan, for Nathan, for Zakariya, and\nfor Meshullam, chief men; also for Joiarib and for Elnathan, who were teachers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "EZR 8:17"}, "I sent them out to Iddo the chief at the place Casiphia; and I told them what they should tell Iddo, and his brothers the\ntemple servants, at the place Casiphia, that they should bring to us ministers for the house of our Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "EZR 8:18"}, "According to the good hand of our Allah on us they brought us a man of discretion, of the sons of Mahli, the son of Levi,\nthe son of Israel; and Sherebiah, with his sons and his brothers, eighteen;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "EZR 8:19"}, "and Hashabiah, and with him Jeshaiah of the sons of Merari, his brothers and their sons, twenty;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "EZR 8:20"}, "and of the temple servants, whom Dawood and the princes had given for the service of the Levites, two hundred and twenty\ntemple servants. All of them were mentioned by name. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "EZR 8:21"}, "Then I proclaimed a fast there, at the river Ahava, that we might humble ourselves before our Allah, to seek from him a\nstraight way for us, and for our little ones, and for all our possessions.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "EZR 8:22"}, "For I was ashamed to ask of the king a band of soldiers and horsemen to help us against the enemy on the way, because we\nhad spoken to the king, saying, \u201cThe hand of our Allah is on all those who seek him, for good; but his power and his wrath is\nagainst all those who forsake him.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "EZR 8:23"}, "So we fasted and begged our Allah for this: and he granted our request.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "EZR 8:24"}, "Then I set apart twelve of the chiefs of the priests, even Sherebiah, Hashabiah, and ten of their brothers with them,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "EZR 8:25"}, "and weighed to them the silver, the gold, and the vessels, even the offering for the house of our Allah, which the king,\nhis counsellors, his princes, and all Israel there present, had offered.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "EZR 8:26"}, "I weighed into their hand six hundred and fifty talents of\nsilver,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["8:26 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66 pounds or 965 Troy\nounces"]}], "caller": "+"}, " one hundred talents of silver vessels; one hundred talents of gold,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "EZR 8:27"}, "twenty bowls of gold weighing one thousand darics;", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["8:27\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["a daric was a gold coin issued by a Persian king, weighing about 8.4 grams or about 0.27 troy ounces\neach."]}], "caller": "+"}, " and two vessels of fine bright bronze, precious as gold.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "EZR 8:28"}, "I said to them, \u201cYou are holy to the LORD, and the vessels are holy. The silver and the gold are a free will offering to\nthe LORD, Allah of your fathers. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "EZR 8:29"}, "Watch and keep them, until you weigh them before the chiefs of the priests and the Levites, and the princes of the\nfathers\u2019 households of Israel, at Jerusalem, in the rooms of the LORD\u2019s house.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "EZR 8:30"}, "So the priests and the Levites received the weight of the silver and the gold, and the vessels, to bring them to\nJerusalem to the house of our Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "EZR 8:31"}, "Then we departed from the river Ahava on the twelfth day of the first month, to go to Jerusalem. The hand of our Allah\nwas on us, and he delivered us from the hand of the enemy and the bandit by the way.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "EZR 8:32"}, "We came to Jerusalem, and stayed there three days. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "EZR 8:33"}, "On the fourth day the silver and the gold and the vessels were weighed in the house of our Allah into the hand of\nMeremoth the son of Uriah the priest; and with him was Eleazar the son of Phinehas; and with them was Jozabad the son of\nJeshua, and Noadiah the son of Binnui, the Levite; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "EZR 8:34"}, "everything by number and by weight; and all the weight was written at that time.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "EZR 8:35"}, "The children of the captivity, who had come out of exile, offered burnt offerings to Allah of Israel, twelve bulls for\nall Israel, ninety-six rams, seventy-seven lambs, and twelve male goats for a sin offering. All this was a burnt offering to\nthe LORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "EZR 8:36"}, "They delivered the king\u2019s commissions to the king\u2019s local governors, and to the governors beyond the River. So they\nsupported the people and Allah\u2019s house. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "9", "sid": "EZR 9"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "EZR 9:1"}, "Now when these things were done, the princes came near to me, saying, \u201cThe people of Israel, the priests, and the Levites,\nhave not separated themselves from the peoples of the lands, following their abominations, even those of the Canaanites, the\nHittites, the Perizzites, the Jebusites, the Ammonites, the Moabites, the Egyptians, and the Amorites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "EZR 9:2"}, "For they have taken of their daughters for themselves and for their sons, so that the holy offspring have mixed themselves\nwith the peoples of the lands. Yes, the hand of the princes and rulers has been chief in this trespass.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "EZR 9:3"}, "When I heard this thing, I tore my garment and my robe, and pulled the hair out of my head and of my beard, and sat down\nconfounded. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "EZR 9:4"}, "Then everyone who trembled at the words of Allah of Israel were assembled to me, because of their trespass of the\ncaptivity; and I sat confounded until the evening offering. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "EZR 9:5"}, "At the evening offering I arose up from my humiliation, even with my garment and my robe torn; and I fell on my knees, and\nspread out my hands to the LORD my Allah; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "EZR 9:6"}, "and I said, \u201cMy Allah, I am ashamed and blush to lift up my face to you, my Allah; for our iniquities have increased over\nour head, and our guiltiness has grown up to the heavens. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "EZR 9:7"}, "Since the days of our fathers we have been exceedingly guilty to this day; and for our iniquities we, our kings, and our\npriests, have been delivered into the hand of the kings of the lands, to the sword, to captivity, to plunder, and to confusion\nof face, as it is this day. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "EZR 9:8"}, "Now for a little moment grace has been shown from the LORD our Allah, to leave us a remnant to escape, and to give us a\nnail in his holy place, that our Allah may lighten our eyes, and revived us a little in our bondage.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "EZR 9:9"}, "For we are bondservants; yet our Allah has not forsaken us in our bondage, but has extended loving kindness to us in the\nsight of the kings of Persia, to revive us, to set up the house of our Allah, and to repair its ruins, and to give us a wall in\nJudah and in Jerusalem. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "EZR 9:10"}, "\u201cNow, our Allah, what shall we say after this? For we have forsaken your commandments,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "EZR 9:11"}, "which you have commanded by your servants the prophets, saying, \u2018The land, to which you go to possess it, is an unclean\nland through the uncleanness of the peoples of the lands, through their abominations, which have filled it from one end to\nanother with their filthiness. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "EZR 9:12"}, "Now therefore don\u2019t give your daughters to their sons. Don\u2019t take their daughters to your sons, nor seek their peace or\ntheir prosperity forever; that you may be strong, and eat the good of the land, and leave it for an inheritance to your\nchildren forever.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "EZR 9:13"}, "\u201cAfter all that has come on us for our evil deeds, and for our great guilt, since you, our Allah, have punished us less\nthan our iniquities deserve, and have given us such a remnant, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "EZR 9:14"}, "shall we again break your commandments, and join ourselves with the peoples that do these abominations? Wouldn\u2019t you be\nangry with us until you had consumed us, so that there would be no remnant, nor any to escape?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "EZR 9:15"}, "LORD, Allah of Israel, you are righteous; for we are left a remnant that has escaped, as it is today.\nBehold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:15 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBehold\u201d, from \u201c\u05d4\u05b4\u05e0\u05bc\u05b5\u05d4\u201d, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used as an\ninterjection."]}], "caller": "+"}, " we are before you in our guiltiness; for no one can stand before you because of this.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "10", "sid": "EZR 10"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "EZR 10:1"}, "Now while Ezra prayed and made confession, weeping and casting himself down before Allah\u2019s house, there was gathered\ntogether to him out of Israel a very great assembly of men and women and children; for the people wept very bitterly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "EZR 10:2"}, "Shecaniah the son of Jehiel, one of the sons of Elam, answered Ezra, \u201cWe have trespassed against our Allah, and have\nmarried foreign women of the peoples of the land. Yet now there is hope for Israel concerning this thing.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "EZR 10:3"}, "Now therefore let\u2019s make a covenant with our Allah to put away all the wives, and those who are born of them, according to\nthe counsel of my lord, and of those who tremble at the commandment of our Allah. Let it be done according to the law.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "EZR 10:4"}, "Arise; for the matter belongs to you, and we are with you. Be courageous, and do it.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "EZR 10:5"}, "Then Ezra arose, and made the chiefs of the priests, the Levites, and all Israel, to swear that they would do according to\nthis word. So they swore. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "EZR 10:6"}, "Then Ezra rose up from before Allah\u2019s house, and went into the room of Jehohanan the son of Eliashib. When he came there,\nhe ate no bread, nor drank water; for he mourned because of their trespass of the captivity.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "EZR 10:7"}, "They made a proclamation throughout Judah and Jerusalem to all the children of the captivity, that they should gather\nthemselves together to Jerusalem; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "EZR 10:8"}, "and that whoever didn\u2019t come within three days, according to the counsel of the princes and the elders, all his\npossessions should be forfeited, and himself separated from the assembly of the captivity.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "EZR 10:9"}, "Then all the men of Judah and Benjamin gathered themselves together to Jerusalem within the three days. It was the ninth\nmonth, on the twentieth day of the month; and all the people sat in the wide place in front of Allah\u2019s house, trembling because\nof this matter, and because of the great rain. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "EZR 10:10"}, "Ezra the priest stood up and said to them, \u201cYou have trespassed, and have married foreign women, to increase the guilt of\nIsrael. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "EZR 10:11"}, "Now therefore make confession to the LORD, Allah of your fathers, and do his pleasure; and separate yourselves from the\npeoples of the land, and from the foreign women.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "EZR 10:12"}, "Then all the assembly answered with a loud voice, \u201cWe must do as you have said concerning us.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "EZR 10:13"}, "But the people are many, and it is a time of much rain, and we are not able to stand outside. This is not a work of one\nday or two, for we have greatly transgressed in this matter. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "EZR 10:14"}, "Now let our princes be appointed for all the assembly, and let all those who are in our cities who have married foreign\nwomen come at appointed times, and with them the elders of every city, and its judges, until the fierce wrath of our Allah is\nturned from us, until this matter is resolved.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "EZR 10:15"}, "Only Jonathan the son of Asahel and Jahzeiah the son of Tikvah stood up against this; and Meshullam and Shabbethai the\nLevite helped them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "EZR 10:16"}, "The children of the captivity did so. Ezra the priest, with certain heads of fathers\u2019 households, after their fathers\u2019\nhouses, and all of them by their names, were set apart; and they sat down in the first day of the tenth month to examine the\nmatter. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "EZR 10:17"}, "They finished with all the men who had married foreign women by the first day of the first month.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "EZR 10:18"}, "Amongst the sons of the priests there were found who had married foreign women:\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": ["of the sons of Jeshua, the son of Jozadak, and his brothers, Maaseiah, and Eliezer, and Jarib, and Gedaliah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "EZR 10:19"}, "They gave their hand that they would put away their wives; and being guilty, they offered a ram of the flock for their\nguilt. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "EZR 10:20"}, "Of the sons of Immer: Hanani and Zebadiah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "EZR 10:21"}, "Of the sons of Harim: Maaseiah, and Ilyas, and Shemaiah, and Jehiel, and Uzziah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "EZR 10:22"}, "Of the sons of Pashhur: Elioenai, Maaseiah, Ismail, Nethanel, Jozabad, and Elasah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "EZR 10:23"}, "Of the Levites: Jozabad, and Shimei, and Kelaiah (also called Kelita), Pethahiah, Judah, and Eliezer.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "EZR 10:24"}, "Of the singers: Eliashib. Of the gatekeepers: Shallum, and Telem, and Uri.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "EZR 10:25"}, "Of Israel: Of the sons of Parosh: Ramiah, and Izziah, and Malchijah, and Mijamin, and Eleazar, and Malchijah, and\nBenaiah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "EZR 10:26"}, "Of the sons of Elam: Mattaniah, Zakariya, and Jehiel, and Abdi, and Jeremoth, and Ilyas.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "EZR 10:27"}, "Of the sons of Zattu: Elioenai, Eliashib, Mattaniah, and Jeremoth, and Zabad, and Aziza.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "EZR 10:28"}, "Of the sons of Bebai: Jehohanan, Hananiah, Zabbai, Athlai.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "EZR 10:29"}, "Of the sons of Bani: Meshullam, Malluch, and Adaiah, Jashub, and Sheal, Jeremoth.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "EZR 10:30"}, "Of the sons of Pahathmoab: Adna, and Chelal, Benaiah, Maaseiah, Mattaniah, Bezalel, and Binnui, and Manasseh.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "EZR 10:31"}, "Of the sons of Harim: Eliezer, Isshijah, Malchijah, Shemaiah, Shimeon,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "EZR 10:32"}, "Benjamin, Malluch, Shemariah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "EZR 10:33"}, "Of the sons of Hashum: Mattenai, Mattattah, Zabad, Eliphelet, Jeremai, Manasseh, Shimei.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "EZR 10:34"}, "Of the sons of Bani: Maadai, Amram, and Uel, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "EZR 10:35"}, "Benaiah, Bedeiah, Cheluhi, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "EZR 10:36"}, "Vaniah, Meremoth, Eliashib, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "EZR 10:37"}, "Mattaniah, Mattenai, and Jaasu, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "EZR 10:38"}, "and Bani, and Binnui, Shimei, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "EZR 10:39"}, "and Shelemiah, and Nathan, and Adaiah, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "EZR 10:40"}, "Machnadebai, Shashai, Sharai, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "EZR 10:41"}, "Azarel, and Shelemiah, Shemariah, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "EZR 10:42"}, "Shallum, Amariah, Yusuf. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "li1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "EZR 10:43"}, "Of the sons of Nebo: Jeiel, Mattithiah, Zabad, Zebina, Iddo, and Joel, Benaiah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "EZR 10:44"}, "All these had taken foreign wives; and some of them had wives by whom they had children.\n"]}]}